<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/brownReferenceArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The brown reference areas indicate hazards other than those evoked by torrents and avalanches (e.g. stone fall and slide areas)."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/torrentCatchmentAreas> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A torrential catchment area comprises the area of the torrent, its tributaries and its alluvial fan. Torrents are perennial or partially active waters. They are characterized by sediment transport, debris flows and woody debris."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
