<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/redHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "red hazard zone"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/yellowHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "An additional denomination of exposed elements."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/partiallyRelevantArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Raumrelevanter Bereich"@de <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#hasTopConcept> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/brownReferenceArea> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/yellowHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "In gelben Gefahrenzonen ist die dauerhafte Nutzung für Siedlungs- und Transportzwecke durch Lawinen/sturzflutartiges Hochwasser beeinträchtigt. Das Bauen in diesen Gebieten ist nur unter besonderen Auflagen möglich."@de <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/avalancheCatchmentArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The avalanche catchment area indicates the eligibility of an avalanche to be fed, the area in which it breaks off and the area in which it deposits. A snow mass with typically a volume greater than 100 m³ and a minimum length of 50 meters that slides rapidly downhill."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/yellowHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/torrentCatchmentAreas> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Ein Wildbach (im Sinne des § 99 Abs. 1 ForstG) ist ein dauernd oder zeitweise fließendes Gewässer, das durch rasch eintretende und nur kurze Zeit dauernde Anschwellungen Feststoffe aus seinem Einzugsgebiet oder aus seinem Bachbett in gefahrdrohendem Ausmaße entnimmt, diese mit sich führt und innerhalb oder außerhalb seines Bettes ablagert oder einem anderen Gewässer zuführt. Das Einzugsgebiet eines Wildbaches (im Sinne des § 99 Abs. 3 ForstG) ist die Fläche des von diesem und seinen Zuflüssen entwässerten Niederschlagsgebietes sowie der Ablagerungsbereich des Wildbaches."@de <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/redHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/yellowHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/redHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "In red hazard zones the threat due to snow avalanches /torrential floods is so high that permanent settlement is not possible or only possible with a disproportionately high expenditure. The construction of new buildings is not recommended."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/brownReferenceArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "brownReferenceArea" <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/partiallyRelevantArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/torrentCatchmentAreas> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/nz> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/redHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/planArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The plan area defines the municipality or parts of a municipality for which the hazard zone map was elaborated."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
