<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "specific exposed element type of WLV"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/yellowHazardZone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "In yellow hazard zones the permanent use for settlement and transport purposes is impaired by snow avalanches /torrential floods. Building in these areas is only possible with specific building control requirements"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/blueReservationArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "blue reservation area"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/avalancheCatchmentArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Das Lawinen-Einzugsgebiet kennzeichnet den Nähr-, Abbruch- und Ablagerungsbereich einer Lawine. Eine Schneemasse mit typischerweise einem Volumen von mehr als 100 m³ und einer Mindestlänge von 50 Metern, die schnell talwärts rutscht."@de <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV/partiallyRelevantArea> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "patially relevant area"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/specificExposedElementTypeWLV:1> .
